                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9275.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Vice
                        Consul <persName type="to">Silliman</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Use every available means to deliver following telegraphic instructions to
                    American Consul Torreon: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Please see at once those in authority at Torreon and say that Department
                            is informed that seven Englishmen, forty Frenchmen, some Spanish and
                            Italians and about forty Germans are detained there against their will
                            and not allowed to leave. Make clear to the authorities that we are
                            obligated to foreign nations to extend to other nationals the same
                            protection that we extend to American citizens and that we therefore
                            demand that all foreigners desiring to leave shall be permitted to go
                            unmolested. Report fully any objections which may be made or failure to
                            carry out these instructions by the authorities.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
